                    <p>Marijuana has been legalalized in Minnesota, am I still being tested for THC on a drug test for my job?</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer isHidden">
                    <p>Many businesses, including the federal government still test for THC. If your employer's drug policy requires their employees to not use marijuana then they yes you may be tested for THC.  Many employers are rewriting their policies as the laws change, so make sure you communicate with your employer on their current policies.</p>
